This small project uses docker and Node Red in a cloud application as watchdog function to home assistant
Home Assistant is expected to ping cloud Node Red every 5min maximum otherwise Node Red will switch on a tuya relay (NC contact) to recycle the Home Assistant PI power.

Get values from https://platform.tuya.com/cloud
In cloud app, go to Settings â†’ Environment and create variables:
Use below Environment Variables in Node-RED
Name	              Value
TUYA_DEVICE_ID	    your device ID
TUYA_ACCESS_ID	    your Tuya Access ID
TUYA_ACCESS_SECRET	your Tuya Access Secret
TUYA_REGION	        your Tuya region (e.g., EU)
PUSHOVER_USER	      your Pushover user key
PUSHOVER_TOKEN	    your Pushover API token
